Video_Title: DIY How to crochet Miu Miu shorts #crochet #gantsilyo
Video_Description:
Materials:
4.2 mm hk
multi-color yarn
scissors âœ‚ï¸ 
darning needle 
stitch marker 
measuring tape
pin

Crochet abbreviations;
double crochet- dc
single crochet- sc
stitch/ stitches- st sts
chain/ chains- ch chs
repeat- rep.
hook- hk
 
Measure around your thigh not fit or tight and  add 1 more inch mine is 20 + 1 inch= 21 inches 
21 inches equivalent of 93 chains.

Panel 1
chain 93,  1 dc 4th st from the hk
Row2  to Row4; ch 2 turn, 1 dc in each st ( chain 2 doesn't count as a st.)
Row5- ch 2 and turn, 1 dec , 1 dc in each st till you have 4 sts left then 2 dec
Row6- ch 2 turn, 2 dec , 1 dc in each st till you have 2 sts left then 1 dec
Row7 - rep row 5
Row8- rep row 6
Row9- rep row 5
Row10 to 25; ch 2 turn, 1 dc in each st 
Row26- ch1 turn, 1 sc in each st, ch1 and fasten off

Panel 2
ch 93, 1 dc 4th st from the hk
Row2 to Row4; ch 2 turn, 1 dc in each st 
Row5- ch 2 turn, 2 dec, 1 dc in each st till you have 2 sts left then 1 dec
Row6- ch 2 turn, 1 dec, 1 dc in each st till you have 4 sts left then 2 dec
Row7- rep row 5
Row8- rep row 6
Row9- rep row 5
Row10 to Row25; ch 2 turn, 1 dc in each st 
Row26- ch 1 turn, 1 sc in each st , ch 1 and fasten off

For the string;
chain 250 slip st 2nd chain from hk
slip stitch in each chain, ch 1 and fasten off

Video_Title: Miu Miu "Private Wishes" Holiday Campaign
Video_Description:
An exploration of private wishes is the focus of the Miu Miu holiday campaign. 
A perfectly formed collection is designed to appeal to our personal fantasies, all of them different, individual, gently provocative. A minimal, even utilitarian aesthetic is juxtaposed with archetypically feminine surface embellishment and gesture. A conversation between clothing reduced to its beautiful essence and a quietly celebratory frivolity ensues.

Proportion is played with as clothing is slashed, spliced and apparently contradictory elements are merged: the oversized and the miniaturized; the buttoned up and the undone; the masculine and the feminine; the outside and the inside come together in a manner that is marginally skewed, studiously disorienting, conveying the tension between the real and the unreal that lies deep within us all. Fashion is our uniform, there to serve, but it is also enriching, aspirational, playful: a naked sandal with a glitter heel; a pliant ballerina scattered with gold; an iconic bag, big or small, in purest white, inkiest black or reflective; a soulful pearl nestling in a cradle of polished brass.

The Miu Miu holiday campaign is both a mirror of the time and a dreamscape, inward looking â€“ private â€“ but an outward looking reflection of innermost thoughts. The spaces the protagonists inhabit are their own. But where are they exactly? At once unmistakeably human but very slightly out of reach, it is left to our imagination to decide. 

The Miu Miu Private Wishes campaign features actor and model Esther McGregor, model Mona Tougaard and actor You-mi Lee. 

Talent: Esther McGregor, Mona Tougaard, You-mi Lee
Art Direction: Lina Kutsovskaya/Be Good Studios
Photographer: Tyrone Lebon
Stylist: Lotta Volkova

Video_Title: Miu Miu TVğŸ’—#ngÃ¢nÄ‘ora#miumiutv
Upcycled by Miu Miu | Fall/Winter 2022 Collection
Video_Description:
In continuing pursuit of sustainable ideologies and giving new life to pre-owned and pre-loved clothing, the Upcycled by Miu Miu initiative continues with a limited edition of leather jackets, specially created and shown on the runway for the Fall/Winter 2022 season. No more than 50 jackets will ever be produced. Each has been carefully sourced from vintage markets across the world, then re-worked â€“ re- fashioned â€“ by Miu Miu and finished in the atelier by hand.

Embodying the paradox at the heart of Miu Miu, the iconic silhouette of this garment, which has long been associated with predominantly male subculture and rebel youth, is embellished with feminine, Twenties-inspired collars in contrasting materials. Equally expressive of the Miu Miu name, and rooted in the tropes of the womenswear wardrobe, is the apparently contradictory presence of stylized flowers, precious crystal, python-print leather and satin ribbon trim.

The accompanying campaign plays on our preconceptions of the masculine perfecto still further. Shot accompanied by shiny vintage motorcycles, gleaming metal and inky rubber, in an anonymous urban subway, it stars actors and model Ever Anderson, Esther McGregor and Mame Bineta Sane. Where are these characters headed? And what will they do once they get there?

Upcycled by Miu Miu leather jackets not only tell the story of the person â€“ or people â€“ who once wore them but also offer the possibility of new stories, present and future, once purchased and worn anew.

Carla is pregnant and naked, just like in the photos where her mother poses pregnant with Carla herself. Sunlight streams through the windows. We see Super 8 shots of grandparents, uncles, aunts, fathers, great-grandparents; smiling, sewing, reciting poetry. Then, we see a young woman grow from the 60s to the present day, passing through the 80s, crossing the thresholds of femininity and history, until she meets Carla pregnant next to the blue sky of the Catalan coast.

CARTA A MI MADRE PARA MI HIJO (LETTER TO MY MOTHER FOR MY SON), directed by #CarlaSimon, is the 24th commission from Miu Miu Womenâ€™s Tales. The acclaimed short-film series invites todayâ€™s most profound and original female directors to investigate vanity and femininity in the 21st century.

Carla SimÃ³n (b.1986) is a Spanish film director. Her 2017 Catalan-language debut film, Summer 1993, became Spain's candidate for Best Foreign Film . Her most recent feature, AlcarrÃ s â€” about the disappearance of traditional peach-harvesting activities in Catalonia â€” won the Golden Bear at the 72nd Berlinale, becoming the first Catalan-language film to do so. 

"CARTA A MI MADRE PARA MI HIJO (Letter to My Mother for My Son)" features veteran actress #AngelaMolina, who has worked with directors such as Luis BuÃ±uel, Pedro AlmodÃ³var, Bigas Lunas and Ridley Scott; #CeciliaGomez, known for her roles in Domingo, The Plague and Down There; and #AinetJounou, who stars in AlcarrÃ s and the forthcoming Paula Ortiz directed Teresa.  

Both of Carla SimÃ³nâ€™s parents died of AIDS when she was just six years old, and because of this, SimÃ³n has scarce memories of them as adults. â€œWith this film for Miu Miu Womenâ€™s Tales, I want to give my son what I didnâ€™t have: a family history.â€ For SimÃ³n, there is a special role that films play in peopleâ€™s inner lives: â€œCinema has the power to repair what is missing.â€ On the topic of Womenâ€™s Tales as a platform for female-led filmmaking, SimÃ³n remarks, â€œItâ€™s very important in the creative process to question things, on set, with your team. I believe women directors are introducing this, and itâ€™s very positive â€” not just for women, but for men, tooâ€.

Fragmentary and fleeting, Carta a mi madre para mi hijo (Letter to My Mother for My Son) is a homage to the filmmakerâ€™s family thatâ€™s partly fictional and entirely heartfelt. â€œIâ€™m an optimist,â€ SimÃ³n says, and her new film is full of tender hope in the midst of loss. It is a touching reminder that understanding who we are requires a lifelong process, piecing together real and imagined memories of the past, in order to compose a picture of the future. 

Carla Simonâ€™s new episode for Womenâ€™s Tales will be premiered at the Venice Film Festivalâ€™s Giornate degli Autori on September 3rd 2022, along with a screening of House Comes with a Bird by Janicza Bravo. The short is afterwards available on Miu Miu digital channels.

Miu Miu Womenâ€™s Tales #24 â€“ Carta A Mi Madre Para Mi Hijo
Video_Description:
Carla is pregnant and naked, just like in the photos where her mother poses pregnant with Carla herself. Sunlight streams through the windows. We see Super 8 shots of grandparents, uncles, aunts, fathers, great-grandparents; smiling, sewing, reciting poetry. Then, we see a young woman grow from the 60s to the present day, passing through the 80s, crossing the thresholds of femininity and history, until she meets Carla pregnant next to the blue sky of the Catalan coast.

CARTA A MI MADRE PARA MI HIJO (LETTER TO MY MOTHER FOR MY SON), directed by #CarlaSimon, is the 24th commission from Miu Miu Womenâ€™s Tales. The acclaimed short-film series invites todayâ€™s most profound and original female directors to investigate vanity and femininity in the 21st century.

Carla SimÃ³n (b.1986) is a Spanish film director. Her 2017 Catalan-language debut film, Summer 1993, became Spain's candidate for Best Foreign Film . Her most recent feature, AlcarrÃ s â€” about the disappearance of traditional peach-harvesting activities in Catalonia â€” won the Golden Bear at the 72nd Berlinale, becoming the first Catalan-language film to do so. 

"CARTA A MI MADRE PARA MI HIJO (Letter to My Mother for My Son)" features veteran actress #AngelaMolina, who has worked with directors such as Luis BuÃ±uel, Pedro AlmodÃ³var, Bigas Lunas and Ridley Scott; #CeciliaGomez, known for her roles in Domingo, The Plague and Down There; and #AinetJounou, who stars in AlcarrÃ s and the forthcoming Paula Ortiz directed Teresa.  

Both of Carla SimÃ³nâ€™s parents died of AIDS when she was just six years old, and because of this, SimÃ³n has scarce memories of them as adults. â€œWith this film for Miu Miu Womenâ€™s Tales, I want to give my son what I didnâ€™t have: a family history.â€ For SimÃ³n, there is a special role that films play in peopleâ€™s inner lives: â€œCinema has the power to repair what is missing.â€ On the topic of Womenâ€™s Tales as a platform for female-led filmmaking, SimÃ³n remarks, â€œItâ€™s very important in the creative process to question things, on set, with your team. I believe women directors are introducing this, and itâ€™s very positive â€” not just for women, but for men, tooâ€.

Fragmentary and fleeting, Carta a mi madre para mi hijo (Letter to My Mother for My Son) is a homage to the filmmakerâ€™s family thatâ€™s partly fictional and entirely heartfelt. â€œIâ€™m an optimist,â€ SimÃ³n says, and her new film is full of tender hope in the midst of loss. It is a touching reminder that understanding who we are requires a lifelong process, piecing together real and imagined memories of the past, in order to compose a picture of the future. 

Carla Simonâ€™s new episode for Womenâ€™s Tales will be premiered at the Venice Film Festivalâ€™s Giornate degli Autori on September 3rd 2022, along with a screening of House Comes with a Bird by Janicza Bravo. The short is afterwards available on Miu Miu digital channels.
From September 5th, "CARTA A MI MADRE PARA MI HIJO (Letter to My Mother for My Son)" will be available to stream on MUBI globally.

The collection of sunglasses presents a wide selection of eyewear with alluring cat-eye styles, sensuous feminine silhouettes, and oversized designs.  

There should be markings on the inside of the left arm with the sizing information. It may have rubbed off but a bit of shimmer eye shadow may make photographed the rubbed markings on both arms more visible.

There should also be an engraved imprint on the inside of the upper right side of the right lens. Again, eye shadow may help it to show better.  

Designer sunglasses can set you back anything from a couple of hundred dollars to a couple of thousand dollars. The world's most expensive sunnies from Chopard are adorned with diamonds and gold, costing as much as a house!

 

The eyewear market is big business so it's not surprising that cheap replicas of sunglasses are flooding the market (trivia alert: Ray-Ban shades are the most highly copied). Earlier in 2019, an OECD report found that trade in counterfeit and pirated goods now stands at 3.3% of global trade.

 

While some fakes are easy to spot a mile away, imitations are becoming increasingly sophisticated. In industry parlance, they're 'confusingly similar'. So if you're in the market for a genuine designer pair, how do you tell if sunglasses are fake?
